abstract: The Georgia Democrat is focusing on voting rights and says she will decide by late March or early April whether to run for president, senator or governor.
snippet: The Georgia Democrat is focusing on voting rights and says she will decide by late March or early April whether to run for president, senator or governor.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Pick a strategy Democrats are considering ahead of 2020, and Stacey Abrams’s narrow loss in the Georgia governor’s race serves either as a blueprint or a warning sign.

headline_main: Stacey Abrams, After Narrow Loss, Has Some Decisions to Make
headline_print_headline: After Her Narrow Loss, Abrams Takes Stock and Regroups

abstract: The former secretary of state told a New York television station that she would continue to speak out on issues, saying, “I’m not going anywhere.”
snippet: The former secretary of state told a New York television station that she would continue to speak out on issues, saying, “I’m not going anywhere.”
lead_paragraph: Hillary Clinton, the former secretary of state and first lady who lost the White House to Donald J. Trump in 2016, said officially on Monday what has been unofficially clear for months: She is not running for president again in 2020.

abstract: A former governor of Colorado and mayor of Denver, Mr. Hickenlooper is running for president on a more centrist platform than many of his competitors.
snippet: A former governor of Colorado and mayor of Denver, Mr. Hickenlooper is running for president on a more centrist platform than many of his competitors.
lead_paragraph: John Hickenlooper, the former governor of Colorado, faces a basic challenge in the crowded Democratic presidential primary: He is a centrist in a party that’s moving to the left. While he has shifted in some areas, he will still be running to the right of the most prominent candidates, with more of an emphasis on pragmatism than idealism.

headline_main: The Power of the Attorney General

abstract: Senator Chuck Schumer says Senate Democrats plan daily floor speeches on climate change, a special select committee and climate legislation to run on next year — and enact in 2021.
snippet: Senator Chuck Schumer says Senate Democrats plan daily floor speeches on climate change, a special select committee and climate legislation to run on next year — and enact in 2021.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Facing a showdown vote as early as this month over the embattled “Green New Deal,” Senate Democrats are preparing a counteroffensive to make combating climate change a central issue of their 2020 campaigns — a striking shift on an issue they have shied away from for the past decade.

headline_main: Pressed by Climate Activists, Senate Democrats Plan to ‘Go on Offense’
headline_print_headline: In Bid for Millennials, Senate Democrats Plan To Emphasize Climate
byline_original: By Coral Davenport and Sheryl Gay Stolberg

abstract: They can appeal to moderate voters without betraying progressive values.
snippet: They can appeal to moderate voters without betraying progressive values.
lead_paragraph: The energy in the 2020 Democratic campaign has been coming from the left. Candidates are pushing Medicare for All, a Green New Deal, a wealth tax and other ideas that are more progressive than anything a recent Democratic nominee has favored.

abstract: Tony West, Uber’s chief legal officer and a former Justice Department official, is navigating the ride-hailing giant’s numerous legal issues.
snippet: Tony West, Uber’s chief legal officer and a former Justice Department official, is navigating the ride-hailing giant’s numerous legal issues.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Not long after Tony West joined Uber as chief legal officer in November 2017, he began a delicate task: crafting a transparency report to quantify how many people had been sexually assaulted during Uber rides.

abstract: His aides are urging him to talk more about himself. But Mr. Sanders charts his own course. Already there has been a dispute that led to the departure of top consultants.
snippet: His aides are urging him to talk more about himself. But Mr. Sanders charts his own course. Already there has been a dispute that led to the departure of top consultants.
lead_paragraph: He will be talking about himself — at least if his advisers have their way. His top aides are not just white men. And unlike last time, when he enjoyed playing the insurgent foil to an establishment-backed politician, Senator Bernie Sanders is now eagerly projecting himself as the front-runner.
